# AXIOM Progress Reporting (Required)

You are working on an AXIOM project under management oversight.

## Required reading at session start
If not already confirmed this session, read:
- cursor/AXIOM_OPERATING_INSTRUCTIONS.md
- docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md
- progress/CURRENT_STATE.md
- progress/BLOCKERS.md
- progress/WEEK1_LOG.md (during Week 1 onboarding only)

## After every meaningful coding session or task completion
Update these files (append only — never delete history):

1. progress/DAILY_LOG.md — today's work entry
2. progress/CURRENT_STATE.md — rolling project snapshot
3. progress/BLOCKERS.md — if any blocker or management question exists
4. docs/DECISION_LOG.md — if an architectural or scope decision was made

Use the format in progress/TEMPLATE.md.

Each DAILY_LOG entry must include:
- Date
- Work completed
- Files changed
- What is working
- What is not working
- Risks or concerns
- Next recommended step
- Questions for management (if any)

## Rules
- Do not invent AXIOM strategy beyond docs/PROJECT_BRIEF.md and docs/AXIOM_VISION.md
- Do not make major scope or architecture changes without documenting in BLOCKERS.md
- If uncertain about requirements, add a question to BLOCKERS.md instead of guessing
- Before ending a session, ensure progress files are updated and summarize what was logged
